title: Palestinian PM hands resignation to Abbas over Gaza ‘genocide’
description: Palestinian Authority's Prime Minister Mohammad Shtayyeh said on Monday that he had officially submitted his government's resignation to President Mahmoud Abbas.

title: Over 7,250 Palestinians arrested in West Bank since October 7
description: The Commission of Detainees and Ex-Detainees’ Affairs and the Palestinian Prisoner's Society (PPS) said that the Israeli forces detained about 7,255 Palestinian citizens from the West Bank since the beginning of the aggression against the Gaza Strip on October 7, 2023.

title: HRW: Israel blocking aid to Palestinians in violation of ICJ order
description: Israel has failed to comply with an order by the United Nations' top court to provide urgently needed aid to desperate people in the Gaza Strip, Human Rights Watch said Monday, a month after a landmark ruling in The Hague ordered Israel to moderate its war.

title: Thousands in Spain's Zaragoza rally for 'Free Palestine'
description: Thousands of people took to the streets of the Spanish city of Zaragoza in support of “Free Palestine” as Israel prepares to attack Rafah – the last remaining shelter for hundreds of thousands of civilians and the backbone of international aid deliveries.

title: Artists call for Israel to be excluded from Venice Biennale
description: More than 4,000 artists are calling for Israel to be excluded from one of the world’s biggest and most prestigious art exhibits.

title: Hezbollah downs Israeli drone over Lebanese territory
description: The Israeli army confirmed on Monday that Hezbollah had shot down its military drone in Lebanese territory.

title: AU, OIC condemn Israeli violation of intl. law
description: Representatives from the African Union (AU) and the Organization of Islamic Cooperation (OIC) presented compelling arguments at the International Court of Justice (ICJ) regarding Israel’s occupation of Palestinian territories.

title: “The Creature” to go on screen at Media Fright Fest
description: TEHRAN- Iranian short movie “The Creature” by Mohammadreza Yarikia will go on screen at the 13th edition of Media Fright Fest, which will take place in the U.S. on April 5.

title: Tehran Symphony Orchestra to perform “Magic Flute Overture” at Vahdat Hall
description: TEHRAN-Tehran’s Vahdat Hall will host a concert by the Tehran Symphony Orchestra (TSO) conducted by Manouchehr Sahbai on March 7.

title: “A River Called Time” at Iranian bookstores
description: TEHRAN- “A River Called Time” by Mozambican writer Mia Couto has recently been published in Persian.

title: IAF cinematheque to screen Bela Tarr’s “Macbeth”
description: TEHRAN-The cinematheque of the Iranian Artists Forum (IAF) in Tehran will show the 1982 Hungarian film “Macbeth” directed by Bela Tarr, based on the famous tragedy of the same name by William Shakespeare, on Wednesday.

title: Intl. children’s theater festival wraps up in Ardakan
description: TEHRAN- The International Theater Festival for Children and Young Adults in Ardakan concluded its 28th edition with a grand ceremony on Sunday.

title: Raisi sends congratulatory message to Kuwaiti emir
description: TEHRAN- In a message to the Emir of Kuwait Mishal Al-Ahmad Al-Jaber Al-Sabah and the Muslim nation of Kuwait on the occasion of the country’s National Day, Iranian President Ebrahim Raisi has congratulated the Arab country on the 63rd anniversary of its independence.

title: Iraqi PM, Iranian ambassador talk about bilateral ties
description: TEHRAN- Iranian Ambassador Kazem Al Sadegh met with Iraqi Prime Minister Mohammed Shia' Al Sudani in Baghdad to talk about mutual cooperation.

title: Russia does not have any Iranian missiles
description: TEHRAN - In a note, the Iran newspaper analyzed a fake news report by Reuters that Iran had sent ballistic missiles to Russia.

title: Strong voter turnout will safeguard Iran’s national security: military
description: TEHRAN – The spokesman for Iran's Defense Ministry has urged the citizens to exercise their voting rights in the parliamentary elections, highlighting the crucial role of participation in shaping the nation's future.

title: President tells legal team to be assertive in defending Iranian people’s rights
description: TEHRAN – During a meeting on Monday, Iranian President Ebrahim Raisi ordered the Department of Legal Affairs to take an offensive approach in dealing with cases that involve the rights of the Iranian nation.

title: Iran calls for nuclear disarmament of Israel
description: TEHRAN – Iran has sounded the alarm bell over Israel’s possession of deadly nuclear weapons, saying the regime’s conduct shows its nuclear arsenal poses a threat to not only Palestinians but people across the world.

title: Tehran, Damascus highlight significance of implementing joint projects
description: TEHRAN- The Syrian prime minister and Iran’s ambassador to Syria on Monday underscored the need to follow up on the implementation of agreements and memorandums of understanding between Tehran and Damascus based on the timetable in a way that ensures the common interests of both countries.

title: Iran FM laments dire humanitarian situation in Gaza at UN session
description: TEHRAN – During his speech at the 55th session of the United Nations Human Rights Council at Geneva, the Iranian foreign minister voiced concern over the deterioration of the humanitarian situation in the Gaza Strip amid Israel’s onslaught.

title: Hungarian FM says economic ties with Iran possible despite sanctions
description: TEHRAN – Hungary’s minister of foreign affairs and trade has said his country is pursuing economic relations with Iran despite Western sanctions making it challenging to maintain bilateral trade and financial ties.

title: Bibi’s insistence on Rafah assault will mark major failure for the West and intl. system
description: TEHRAN - Rafah is the southernmost city in the Gaza Strip, adjacent to Egypt. Located approximately ۱۰۷ kilometers west of occupied al-Quds (Jerusalem), the city covers an area of less than ۵۵ square kilometers, which expanded to around ۶۴ square kilometers during the recent war due to the settlement of refugees in its vicinity.

title: IRGC chief says Iran does believe Gazans will prevail
description: TEHRAN- The Islamic Republic of Iran, the chief of the Islamic Revolution Guards Corps (IRGC) says, is certain that the Palestinian resistance will prevail against the Israeli regime in the Gaza Strip, where the Tel Aviv regime is perpetrating genocide.

title: Security personnel to safeguard Iran's Friday election
description: TEHRAN – At least 250,000 security personnel from the police, army, IRGC, and Basij will be overseeing the security of ballot boxes and polling stations across the country on Friday, a senior official from the Interior Ministry said on Monday.

title: Fiery Resistance to Gaza Genocide
description: TEHRAN- Domestic backlash to the United States’ unwavering support for Israel’s genocidal war on Gaza once again hit the headlines following the tragic death of an active-duty member of the American Air Force.

title: Iran defeat India at FIBA Asia Cup 2025 qualifier
description: TEHRAN - Iran finished their FIBA Asia Cup 2025 Qualifiers Window 1 campaign unbeaten following an 86-53 beatdown of India, Monday at the K.D. Jadhav Indoor Hall.

title: Isfahan aims to attract surge of Chinese tourists with new initiatives
description: TEHRAN - Isfahan has announced an ambitious plan to attract over 20 million Chinese visitors in a year in a bid to bolster the tourism industry of the province.

title: Nautical committees set to foster tourism
description: TEHRAN – As a substantial step to fortify nautical and coastal tourism, the Director General of Parliament Affairs of Tourism Ministry has revealed the establishment of water tourism committees in alignment with the 7th National Development Plan.

title: Iranian hospitality wins Chinese influencer’s heart
description: TEHRAN – “Traveling to Iran sheds light on the real meaning of the word; Persian”, mentioned by a Chinese social media influencer who recently visited the country, participating in a Fam Tour called “Salam Iran”.

title: Qeshm Island: a journey through Iran’s geological wonderland
description: TEHRAN - Qeshm, the largest island in the Persian Gulf, stands out as one of Iran’s most enchanting destinations.

title: Persepolis part ways with Nabil Bahoui, Shahab Zahedi
description: TEHRAN - Persepolis football club parted company with their forwards Nabil Bahoui and Shahab Zahedi on Monday.

title: TEDPIX drops 16,700 points on Monday
description: TEHRAN- TEDPIX, the main index of the Tehran Stock Exchange (TSE), dropped 16,700 points (0.08 percent) to 2,049,437 on Monday, which is the third day of the Iranian calendar week.

title: Average daily gasoline consumption reaches 132m liters
description: TEHRAN - Average daily gasoline consumption in Iran has reached about 132 million liters, Oil Minister Javad Oji said on Monday.

title: Over 230,000 National Housing Movement units delivered to applicants
description: TEHRAN- The head of the Housing Foundation of Islamic Revolution announced that 230,722 units of the National Housing Movement have been completed and handed over to the applicants, IRNA reported.

title: Water level of Iran’s major dam reservoirs declines 25%
description: TEHRAN – The total volume of water stored behind Iranian dams is currently estimated at 22.41 billion cubic meters, showing a 25 percent decline compared to the previous year, Tasnim News Agency reported.

title: Iran’s port capacity to increase by 200m tons
description: TEHRAN – The container capacity of Iranian ports is going to increase by 200 million tons with the completion of two new ports in the Makran Coasts, namely Makran Port and Persian Gulf Port, according to the Iranian Transport and Urban Development Minister.

title: Iran-Pakistan gas pipeline project recommences after ten-year delay
description: TEHRAN - In a significant step towards enhancing energy cooperation between Pakistan and Iran, Islamabad has given the green light for advancing much-delayed work on the Iran-Pakistan gas pipeline within its territory.

title: Afghan economic delegation visits Iran’s Chabahar free zone
description: TEHRAN - An economic and technical delegation from Afghanistan is visiting the Chabahar Industrial Free Trade Zone to explore trade and investment opportunities in the Iranian port.

title: Iran-Russia Joint Economic Committee meetings kick off in Tehran
description: TEHRAN - The specialized working groups of the 17th Iran-Russia Joint Economic Committee have started meeting in Tehran to discuss areas of cooperation before the main event which is due to be held on Wednesday, February 28.

title: Iran’s nominal power generation capacity exceeds 92,000 MW
description: TEHRAN – The nominal capacity of Iran’s power plants has reached 92,055 megawatts (MW), according to the latest data released by Iran Grid Management Company (IGMC).

title: Iranians proud of beach soccer team
description: TEHRAN - As much as people have distanced themselves from Iran national football team, they have come closer to their national beach soccer team and are proud of them.

title: Iran calls for expanding co-op with WHO EMRO
description: TEHRAN – Health Minister Bahram Einollahi has announced the country’s readiness to foster cooperation with the World Health Organization’s Regional Office for the Eastern Mediterranean.

title: UNRWA forced to 'stretch every dollar' amid $450m budget shortfall
description: The UN agency for Palestinian refugees has been forced to “stretch every dollar” and juggle its finances in order to continue vital work in Gaza after 18 donor countries suspended funding over allegations of links to Hamas, the Guardian reported.

title: Over 3,700 people receive rescue services in two days
description: TEHRAN – The Iranian Red Crescent Society (IRCS) rescued 3,753 individuals trapped in blizzards and floods in 23 provinces over February 24-25.

title: More than 440 rare diseases identified in Iran
description: TEHRAN– A total of 442 rare diseases have been identified in the country according to a recent report by the Rare Disease Foundation.

title: Geo-environmental hazards and disasters affect Persian Gulf coast
description: TEHRAN - A review of the earthquake risk and the possibility of a tsunami caused by it should be carried out on the coasts of the mainland and the islands of the Persian Gulf.

title: Iran’s Olfati takes silver at Gymnastics World Cup
description: TEHRAN – Iran’s Mahdi Olfati claimed a silver medal at the International Gymnastics Federation (FIG)'s World Cup held in Cottbus, Germany.

title: USAF soldier self-immolates outside of Israeli Embassy to protest Gaza ‘genocide’
US Air force pilot sets self on fire in front of Israeli embassy in protest to Gaza war
description: A U.S. military member set himself on fire outside the Israeli embassy in Washington DC on Sunday afternoon in protest against the war in the Gaza Strip.

title: Gaza Reveals Western Hypocrisy
205 idle units revived in Tehran industrial parks since last March
description: TEHRAN – The deputy managing director of Tehran province’s Industrial Parks Company announced that 205 idle production units have been revived in the industrial parks and zones of the province during the current Iranian calendar year (began on March 21, 2023).
